commit.message:
Declare support for Python 3.7

As a software engineer, I'd like to have support for modern versions
of Python declared in setup.py and to have corresponding tests on CI.

Also, I'd like to be able to conveniently run tests
in my local environment, so I want to add a tox config file.

These changes:

 - Add Python 3.7 to setup.py

 - Add Python 3.7 and 3.8-dev to .travis.yml

 - Add tox.ini

 - Drop support for Python 3.4 (end-of-life on 2019-03-19)

Add IntelliJ workspace files.

(Note that in line with best practices this adds only generic and not developer-specific files.)
